<br>
As my eyes ran across the words, my heart began to pound in my chest. I had been trying despreatly to heal Eviahs wounds, to cure her plauged soul, only to be rebuffed by the Dark Man that haunted her dreams and turned them into nightmares. Every time she and I had come closer and became happier, things would suddenly go spiraling out of control. Pain, confusion, suffering, hopelessness and anger would take control. After we would argue and Eviah would break down, my heart would tear just abit more each time. I felt guilty, causing this pain for her.<br>
<br>
Softly setting the note back upon the table, I knew that I would do what it took for Eviah to be cured. I would be her pillar of love, life and hope. I nodded to myself, standing. It would have to be done soon, the Dark One was getting closer and I had a sinking feeling that he was right on our door step... <p>Warden Wildrunner
<br>
Scout of Bristlebane
<br>
Clan of Brothers
<br>
